.NET Core 1.0.name: DiscordVoiceState
.NET Core 1.0.summary: Used to represent a user's voice connection status.

methods.name: Serialize()
methods.summary: Serializes this voice state into a DiscordApiData object.
methods.returns: Returns a new DiscordApiData object with the properties of this voice state.

methods.name: Update(DiscordApiData data)
methods.summary: Updates this voice state with the specified DiscordApiData.

params.value: The data to update this voice state with.

properties.name: Channel
properties.summary: Gets the voice channel this user is in.

properties.name: Guild
properties.summary: Gets the guild the user of this voice state is in.

properties.name: IsSelfDeaf
properties.summary: Gets whether or not this user has deafened themself.

properties.name: IsSelfMute
properties.summary: Gets whether or not this user has muted themself.

properties.name: IsServerDeaf
properties.summary: Gets whether or not this user is server deaf.

properties.name: IsServerMute
properties.summary: Gets whether or not this user is server mute.

properties.name: IsSuppressed
properties.summary: Gets whether or not this user is muted by the active user connected to the API.

properties.name: SessionId
properties.summary: Gets the current session id of this voice state.

properties.name: User
properties.summary: Gets the user this voice state is for.
